Ibn al-Qayyim reported: Abdullah ibn Ahmad said, \u201cI asked my father Ahmad ibn Hanbal about a man who has books, within which are the sayings of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and the companions and the followers, but he cannot distinguish weak and rejected narrations,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33842,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/12\/17\/ahmad-true-love-for-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":21509,"position":5},"title":"Ahmad on Love: True love for Allah seeks no worldly benefits","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 17, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Maruwidhi reported: Imam Ahmad ibn Hanbal, may Allah have mercy on him, was asked about love for the sake of Allah and he said, \u201cIt is that you not love him for the sake of some worldly benefit.\u201d Source: T\u0323abaqa\u0304t al-H\u0323ana\u0304bilah 1\/60 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u0648\u0630\u064a \u0642\u062f \u0633\u0626\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u062d\u0646\u0628\u0644\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/21509","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"